news_obj.content: Actor Puneet Issar revealed that he lost 8 to 10 films following an accident during 'Coolie' shoot involving him and Amitabh Bachchan. "People were quite scared of me after that incident. They said he is an 8th-degree black belt holder," Puneet added. During a fight scene with Puneet, Amitabh suffered a serious internal injury and was rushed to a hospital.
news_obj.title: Lost 8-10 films after 'Coolie' accident, people feared me: Puneet
news_obj.bottom_headline: 'People suddenly forgot that I'm trained artist'

news_obj.content: India aims to blend 30 percent ethanol with gasoline by 2030 to reduce oil imports and environmental impact. Ethanol blending began in 2001 and reached 20 percent by March 2025. Ethanol 100 fuel has also been introduced in select states. While E20 fuel may lower mileage slightly, the program has saved significant foreign currency and crude oil imports.
news_obj.title: Govt targets 10% increase in ethanol petrol blending by 2030

news_obj.content: US National Archives released over 10,000 pages of records related to the 1968 assassination of Senator Robert F Kennedy. The files, released after a directive by US President Donald Trump, mentioned the killer's motives and warnings made prior to attack. "RFK must be disposed of like his brother (President John F Kennedy) was," a handwritten note by the killer read.
news_obj.title: Robert Kennedy assassination files released; mention killer's plans, warnings
news_obj.bottom_headline: Prez John F Kennedy was assassinated in 1963

news_obj.content: Following RCB's loss to PBKS, former India opener Virender Sehwag said RCB batters played reckless shots and that at least one of them should've used common sense. "If they had wickets in hand, they could've reached 110 or 120 in 14 overs, which would've given them a chance to fight," he added. RCB were restricted to 95 in 14 overs.

news_obj.content: Delhi CM Rekha Gupta has ordered a probe after a four-storey building in the Mustafabad area collapsed on Saturday, killing at least four people. As many as 14 people have been rescued so far, but several others are feared trapped under the rubble. Rescue operations by a team of NDRF, firefighters and Delhi Police are currently underway.
news_obj.title: Delhi CM orders probe into Mustafabad building collapse incident
news_obj.bottom_headline: 'May God grant peace to the departed souls'

news_obj.content: India on Saturday condemned abduction and killing of Hindu leader Bhabesh Chandra in Bangladesh's Dinajpur. "This killing follows a pattern of systematic persecution of Hindu minorities under (Bangladesh's) interim government," said Foreign Ministry. It said the interim government should "live up to its responsibility of protecting all minorities, including Hindus, without inventing excuses".
news_obj.title: Systematic persecution of Hindus: India condemns Hindu leader's killing in B'desh
news_obj.bottom_headline: 'Perpetrators of such crimes roam with impunity'

news_obj.content: The letter sent to Harvard University by US President Donald Trump's government, listing demands on hiring, admissions and curriculum, was "unauthorised", a New York Times report quoted a top official as saying. The official reportedly contacted the university saying the letter was sent by mistake. Harvard rejected the demands, prompting Trump to freeze $2.2 billion in grants to the University.
news_obj.title: Trump govt's letter to Harvard, listing its demands, was sent by mistake: NYT
news_obj.bottom_headline: Letter sent by Trump's antisemitism task force

news_obj.content: The US has reissued a Level 3 travel advisory for Bangladesh and a Level 4 warning for its Chittagong Hill Tracts due to communal violence, crime, and terrorism. US citizens were urged to avoid gatherings and reconsider travel amid ongoing security concerns. Notably, the update came shortly after abduction and killing of Hindu community leader Bhabesh Chandra Roy in Dinajpur.
news_obj.title: US reissues travel advisory for B'desh, warns of communal violence
news_obj.bottom_headline: The advisory also warned of kidnappings

news_obj.content: Trump is studying whether he could fire Federal Reserve Chairman Jerome Powell, whom he accused of "playing politics" by not cutting interest rates. Federal Reserve Act allows dismissing Board members, including Chair, "for cause", historically interpreted as misconduct or incapacity, not disagreements. But a pending Supreme Court case could redefine presidential power over independent agencies.
news_obj.title: Can Trump fire US Fed chief Powell?
news_obj.bottom_headline: Powell said he wouldn't step down voluntarily
news_obj.bottom_text: Powell says the law protects his position

news_obj.content: Volvo Group announced that it would lay off hundreds of employees from various locations in the US due to demand concerns and market uncertainty amid Donald Trump's tariffs. The company said that the Volvo layoffs will impact 550 to 800 employees at the company's sites in the United States in multiple states.
news_obj.title: Volvo laying off 800 employees in US amid Trump tariffs
